				<div class="dablink">"Arabic" redirects here. For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Arabic_(disambiguation)" title="Arabic (disambiguation)" class="mw-redirect">Arabic (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<table class="infobox noprint selfref" cellpadding="3" style="clear: right; width: 27em; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 83%; line-height: 1.2em">
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: middle; width: 65px">
<div class="center">
<div class="floatnone"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Arabic_albayancalligraphy.svg/65px-Arabic_albayancalligraphy.svg.png" width="65" height="29" /></div>
</div>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: middle"><b>This article contains <strong class="selflink">Arabic text</strong>, written from right to left in a cursive style with some letters joined.</b> Without proper <a href="/wiki/Help:Arabic" title="Help:Arabic">rendering support</a>, you may see unjoined Arabic letters written left-to-right instead of right-to-left or other symbols instead of <a href="/wiki/Arabic_script" title="Arabic script" class="mw-redirect">Arabic script</a>.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<table class="infobox" style="width: 22em; text-align: left; font-size: 88%; line-height: 1.5em">
<tr>
<th colspan="3" style="text-align: center; font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; color: black; background-color: yellow">Arabic</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="3" style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold; color: black; background-color: yellow">العربية <i><span title="DIN 31635 Arabic" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">al-ʿarabiyyah</span></i></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="vertical-align: middle"><b><span title="DIN 31635 Arabic" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">al-ʿArabiyyah</span></b> in written Arabic (<a href="/wiki/Naskh_(script)" title="Naskh (script)">Naskh</a> script)</th>
<td colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/File:Arabic_albayancalligraphy.svg" class="image"><img alt="Arabic albayancalligraphy.svg" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Arabic_albayancalligraphy.svg/200px-Arabic_albayancalligraphy.svg.png" width="200" height="88" /></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Pronunciation</th>
<td colspan="2"><span title="Pronunciation in IPA" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_Arabic" title="Wikipedia:IPA for Arabic">[æl ʕɑrɑˈbijjɐ]</a></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Spoken in</th>
<td>Primarily in the <a href="/wiki/Arab_states" title="Arab states" class="mw-redirect">Arab states</a> of the Middle East and North Africa;<br />
<a href="/wiki/Liturgical_language" title="Liturgical language" class="mw-redirect">liturgical language</a> of <a href="/wiki/Islam" title="Islam">Islam</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Total speakers</th>
<td colspan="2">Approx. 340 million native speakers<sup id="cite_ref-Proch_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Proch-0"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th><a href="/wiki/Language_family" title="Language family">Language family</a></th>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align:left"><a href="/wiki/Afro-Asiatic_languages" title="Afro-Asiatic languages" class="mw-redirect">Afro-Asiatic</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:15px;padding-left:0">
<li><a href="/wiki/Semitic_languages" title="Semitic languages">Semitic</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:5px;padding-left:0">
<li><a href="/wiki/Central_Semitic_languages" title="Central Semitic languages">Central Semitic</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:5px;padding-left:0">
<li><a href="/wiki/Arabic_languages" title="Arabic languages">Arabic</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:5px;padding-left:0">
